      <td width=\"300\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n            <td width=\"70\" align=\"center\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n            <td width=\"70\" align=\"center\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n            <td width=\"70\" align=\"center\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td width=\"300\"><strong>Totaal Punten</strong></td>\r\n            <td width=\"70\" align=\"center\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n            <td width=\"70\" align=\"center\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n            <td width=\"70\" align=\"center\"><strong>#c21#</strong></td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td width=\"300\"><strong>Kale huurprijs</strong></td>\r\n            <td width=\"70\" align=\"center\"></td>\r\n            <td width=\"70\" align=\"center\"></td>\r\n            <td width=\"70\" align=\"center\"></td>\r\n            <td width=\"70\" align=\"left\">&euro; #Kalehuur#</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td width=\"510\" colspan=\"4\">Voorschot op algemene kosten:<br>\r\nBelastingen en heffingen overheid (*), 600,- / jaar<br>\r\nVerwarming gebouw, gebouwbeheer, VVE, 4000,- / jaar<br> \r\nInternet (indien van toepassing), TV signal, 600,- / jaar<br>\r\nSchoonmaak en schoonmaakmiddelen, 1100,- / jaar<br>\r\nKleine herstellingen, begeleiding kleine herstellingen, afschrijvingen, vervangingen, administratiekosten, overigen, onvoorzien, 1500,- / jaar<br>\r\n18 maanden afschrijvingstermijn gemeubileerde kamer (inventaris+arbeid) 1200,- / jaar<br>\r\nHuurder verklaart uitdrukkelijk deze leveringen te accepteren. Huurders kunnen jaarlijks vanaf juli in de huurdersdashboard de werkelijke kosten inzien voor voorgaande jar(en).\r\n           </td>\r\n            <td width=\"70\" align=\"left\">&euro; #Servicekosten#&nbsp;</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td width=\"300\"><strong>Totale Huurprijs</strong></td>\r\n            <td width=\"70\" align=\"center\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n            <td width=\"70\" align=\"center\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n            <td width=\"70\" align=\"center\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n            <td width=\"70\" align=\"left\"><strong>&euro; #TotaalKosten#</strong></td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n(*)Gemeentelijke belastingen zijn volgens definitie van de huurcommissie geen onderdeel van de servicekosten, maar zijn volgens de kantonrechter wel door huurders verschuldigd. Deze belastingen worden door de overheid geïnd bij zowel (hoofdhuurder) als verhuurder. Het door huurder te betalen deel dat bij verhuurder wordt geïnd is onderdeel van de totale huurprijs.\r\n\r\n<page_break>\r\n<h3>Gebruikersverklaring #Woningmerk#</h3>\r\nOndergetekende,<br/>\r\nverklaart bij deze, dat hij/zij in hoedanigheid van gebruiker en huurder van het appartement #Woningmerk#, kamer #Kamermerk#:\r\n<br/><br/>\r\n(1) kennis heeft genomen van het splitsingsreglement en het huishoudelijk reglement van de vereniging van eigenaars;\r\n<br/><br/>\r\n(2) die reglementen alsmede alle overige door de vergadering van eigenaars van deze vereniging gestelde en nog te stellen regels betreffende het gebruik van de gedeelten, die niet bestemd zijn als afzonderlijk geheel te worden gebruikt, strikt en integraal zal naleven;\r\n<br/><br/>\r\n(3) eveneens alle door de vergadering van eigenaars van deze vereniging te stellen regels betreffende het gebruik van het privegedeelte, strikt en integraal zal naveven, tenzij een beroep op die besluiten en bepalingen jegens de ondergetekende in strijd zou zijn met de redelijkheid en billikheid;\r\n<br/><br/>\r\nAldus verklaard en ondertekend,<br/><br/>\r\nPlaats: Amsterdam   Datum: #Startdatum#<br/>\nNaam huurder/gebruiker: #Naam#   E-mail: #Email#  Telefoon: #Phone#<br/><br/>\r\nHandtekening:\r\n<table>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"300\" align=\"center\">_TenantSignHere_</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</table>'),
    (2, 1,'<h2>Rental contract #Kamermerk# #Woningmerk#</h2>\r\n\r\nThis contract contains the following documents: \r\n<table>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td width=\"60\" align=\"center\">1.</td>\r\n            <td>Usage agreement</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td width=\"60\" align=\"center\">2.</td>\r\n            <td>General provisions</td>a\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td width=\"60\" align=\"center\">3.</td>\r\n            <td>Room area specification and rent calculation</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td width=\"60\" align=\"center\">4.</td>\r\n            <td>Inspection / Record Report / inventory</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\nThe undersigned:\r\n<table>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td valign=\"top\" width=\"60\" align=\"center\">1.</td>\r\n            <td width=\"600\">#Verhuurder#, born 17-09-1968 te Paramaribo/Suriname, herein represented by R. Vriesde, choosing office at #Woningmerk#. Also called the land lord,</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td valign=\"top\" width=\"60\" align=\"center\">2.</td>\r\n            <td width=\"600\">#Naam#, born #Geboortedatum#. Also called the tenant,</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\nDeclare to have agreed as follows:<br/>\r\n<br/>\r\n<h3>Article 1.</h3>\r\n<table>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td valign=\"top\" width=\"60\" align=\"center\">1.</td>\r\n            <td width=\"600\">The landlord rents to tenants who accepts rent a room, Brand #Kamermerk#,  including the common areas as defined in Article 3 and in the contractual documents 3 and 4 in the apartment located in #Woningmerk#, the tenant fully known, that it requires no further description.</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td valign=\"top\" width=\"60\" align=\"center\">2.</td>\r\n            <td width=\"600\">This contract is concluded for an indefinite period, commencing  #Startdatum# and ending after termination by either party on the other. Termination must be made via the tenant dashboard at http://My.1stHome.nl and is subject of the statutory deadline (at least <b>one calendar month</b> for tenant, at least three calendar months for landlord). If tenant cancels using the dashboard, the cancellation will be valid after landlord gives confirmation via e-mail.</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td valign=\"top\" width=\"60\" align=\"center\">3.</td>\r\n            <td width=\"600\">The basic rent to be paid by tenant to land lord  is  #Kalehuur# per month, starting on #Startdatum#. The general cost are  #Servicekosten# (for a total of  #TotaalKosten#) for room  #Kamermerk#. In case this agreement does not commence on the first day of month, then tenant will pay for that month:  #TotaalKosten# / total days in month * remaining days in month.</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td valign=\"top\" width=\"60\" align=\"center\">4.</td>\r\n            <td width=\"600\">The total rent should be paid monthly in advance by transfer to account<b> #Rekeningnr#, in name of #Verhuurder#</b> at address: Ghp 2, 2132TG in Hoofddorp, The Netherlands (Bank: ING, Foppingadreef 7, 1102BD Amsterdam), without discount or claim to  compensation. In any case before the first day of the following month in advance, stating name. Any financial shortcomings will at all times remain legally actionable.</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td valign=\"top\" width=\"60\" align=\"center\">4.1</td>\r\n            <td width=\"600\">Non exclusive to the provisions of Article 4, Tenant is advised that late rent payments are handled the following manner:<br/>\r\n            - A week behind: 1st reminder via email and SMS.<br/>\r\n            - Two weeks delay: 2nd reminder via email and SMS.<br/>\r\n            - Three weeks delay: Mechanical block on room entrance. Eur 30,- block removal cost.<br/>\r\n            - Four weeks delay: reminder for 2 times the monthly rent via email and SMS.<br/>\r\n            - Five weeks delay: collection procedure. Cost paid by tenant.<br/>\r\nAfter two late payments, land lord will not give a positive renting declaration for future use.  After three late payments of a week duration, the room entrance may be mechanically blocked with Eur 30,- deblocking charges to be paid by tenant. For each timely rent payment, land lord will increase the deposit return to tenant with Eur #Timelyrentcredit#. With each late rent payment, land lord will deduct from deposit return to tenant Eur #Laterentcharge# </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td valign=\"top\" width=\"60\" align=\"center\">5.</td>\r\n            <td width=\"600\">Insofar as an increase of the rent is not legally limited, the landlord will increase rates and inform tenant at least two months before the date on which the rent is to increase.</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3>Article 2.</h3>\r\n<table>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td valign=\"top\" width=\"60\" align=\"center\">1.</td>\r\n            <td width=\"600\">Apartment and room inventory are made available by the land lord. Any defects, and necessary repairs or replacements are not deductible. The tenant is free to include goods for own account in the apartment.</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td valign=\"top\" width=\"60\" align=\"center\">2.</td>\r\n            <td width=\"600\">The antenna cable subscription fees are paid by Landlord. The cost of the use of additional services, which may be telephone (subscription and call charges), shall be borne by the tenant.</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td valign=\"top\" width=\"60\" align=\"center\">3.</td>\r\n            <td width=\"600\">The tenant is obliged to cover damages caused by his negligence, even if this is due to storm, frost, snow, fire or short circuit, to the satisfaction of the land lord, directly after the damage has occurred.</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td valign=\"top\" width=\"60\" align=\"center\">4.</td>\r\n            <td width=\"600\">The general costs borne by the tenant are on a separate annex to this contract.</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td valign=\"top\" width=\"60\" align=\"center\">5.</td>\r\n            <td width=\"600\">If any apartment appliance fails due to tenants actions beyond normal usage, they will be replaced at tenants expense.</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3>Article 3.</h3>\r\n<table>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td valign=\"top\" width=\"60\" align=\"center\">1.</td>\r\n            <td width=\"600\">The common areas, corridors, balconies, kitchen, bathroom and toilet are biweekly cleaned by the land lord. Tenant is responsible for the cleaning of the room. The common areas may not be used as storage areas, and will be in violation after the first request at the expense of the tenant (s) to be cleared.</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td valign=\"top\" width=\"60\" align=\"center\">2.</td>\r\n            <td width=\"600\">The tenant must take out adequate insurance against damage to his possessions, against fire and consequential damages. For example, water damage due to burst of water pipes.</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td valign=\"top\" width=\"60\" align=\"center\">3.</td>\r\n            <td width=\"600\">The tenant chooses for the execution of this Agreement domicile in the leased property.</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3>Article 4.</h3>\r\n<table>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td valign=\"top\" width=\"60\" align=\"center\">1.</td>\r\n            <td width=\"600\">If the rent is not paid on the due date, collection costs, both judicial and extrajudicial will be borne by the tenant.</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td valign=\"top\" width=\"60\" align=\"center\">2.</td>\r\n            <td width=\"600\">With late payments tenant will be in violation by the mere act of late payment, without a need by landlord to indicate that violation. Landlord has at that point the explicit right to terminate this contract, vacate the room and seek damages at cost to tenant.</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3>Article 5.</h3>\r\n<table>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td valign=\"top\" width=\"60\" align=\"center\">1.</td>\r\n            <td width=\"600\">In case tenant leaves for a longer period without making payment of handing over the keys to the landlord, the latter shall have the right to enter the room and take possession of it.</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3>Article 6.</h3>\r\n<table>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td valign=\"top\" width=\"60\" align=\"center\">1.</td>\r\n            <td width=\"600\">\r\nIf the tenant uses municipal registration,this should be reverted no later than 1 calendar month after notice of cancellation of this contract. The deposit mentioned in article 8 will be returned within 1 month after end date of the contract and after the tenant (1) returns all keys, (2) demonstrates in writing municipal deregistration, (3) has paid his share of government tenant taxes to the main tenant, (4) returns the room as received in its initial state. In case deregistration cannot be demonstrated or tenant chooses to continue registration at this address then a monthly fee of Eur #Registrationcharge# will be due by tenant, for every calender month or part thereof that the registration continues. Tenant specifically allows land lord to check the registration of tenant in the government registry if and when the government facilitates this.\r\n</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Article 7.</h3>\r\n<table>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td valign=\"top\" width=\"60\" align=\"center\">1.</td>\r\n            <td width=\"600\">\r\nTenant receives upon signing of this agreement and first payment the following keys: #SleutelsEN#\r\n</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td valign=\"top\" width=\"60\" align=\"center\">2.</td>\r\n            <td width=\"600\">\r\nTenant is obliged to provide landlord with a copy of identification. Tenant returns the keys at the end of this Agreement to the landlord. In case of loss landlord will replace the keys at a cost of Eur #Lostkeycharge# to be paid by tenant. The single door opening charge will be Eur #Dooropeningcharge# per event. \r\n</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3>Article 8.</h3>\r\n<table>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td valign=\"top\" width=\"60\" align=\"center\">1.</td>\r\n            <td width=\"600\">\r\nThe parties agree: That at the signing of this agreement for a room  #Kamermerk#,   #TotalDeposit# must be paid as deposit by tenant, on which no interest is provided. Although tenant may cancel the contract at any time (taking the cancellation period into account), the prospective renting period is minimal one year. At earlier termination the landlord is entitled to following fees: Eur #cancel3Months# at cancellation within 90 days, Eur #cancel6Months# at cancellation within 6 months, Eur #cancel12Months# at cancellation within 1 year.\r\n</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3>Article 9.</h3>\r\n<table>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td valign=\"top\" width=\"60\" align=\"center\">1.</td>\r\n            <td width=\"600\">\r\nEnergy fair use and waste avoidance. In compliance with Dutch law, \"Huurwet\", \"Warmte Wet\", cost of heating, electricity, gas and (warm) water are borne by tenant and are provided for in the general cost as part of the rental price. This provision for utilities is made specific with maximum \'\'fair use\'\' values below for the whole apartment and individual room:<br/><br/>\r\n(1) Yearly usage Kilo Watt Hours electricity whole apartment: #KwhAppartement#<br/>\r\n(2) Yearly usage m3 warm water whole appartement: #m3WWAppartement#<br/>\r\n(3) Yearly usage m3 cooking gas: #m3GasAppartement#<br/>\r\n(4) Yearly usage heating units general areas apartment: #WE_Alg# (Meternr: #Meternr_Alg#)<br/>\r\n(5) Yearly usage heating units room #Kamermerk#: #WE_kamer# (Meternr: #Meternr_kamer#)\r\n</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td valign=\"top\" width=\"60\" align=\"center\">2.</td>\r\n            <td width=\"600\">\r\nTenant should regularly check used units on the sensors present in the apartment. Tenant retains their pro-rata heating units from the contract start date. For example: with contract start date April 1, tenant can use following heating units: #WE_kamer# yearly units / 12 months * 9 months (apr-dec), irrespective of meter value on contract start date, even if this value is above #WE_kamer#.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\nFor usage above these pro rata values, land lord has the explicit right to charge additional cost, split over all tenants for general values, and directly to tenant for room specific values, according to table below:<br/>\r\nPer heating unit: Eur #EurPerWE#<br/>\r\nPer m3 gas: Eur 0.65<br/>\r\nPer Kwh electricity: Eur 0.70<br/>\r\nPer m3 warm water: #EurPerM3WW#<br/>\r\n<br/>\r\nThis extra cost correction may be done on a monthtly basis with monthly averages derived from total values. Land lord also has the right to change above values if general market price levels change for electricity (Kwh) or gas (m3).\r\n</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Article 10.</h3>\r\nTo the extent not otherwise provided in this Agreement, the parties will observe the provisions of the Civil Code concerning tenancies.<br/>\r\n<br/>\r\nThus in duplicate and signed at Amsterdam, d.d. #Startdatum#<br/>\r\n<br/>\r\nThe land lord,                                                                         The tenant,<br/>\r\n<br/>\r\n<table>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td valign=\"top\" width=\"300\" align=\"center\">_SignHere_</td>\r\n            <td valign=\"top\" width=\"300\" align=\"center\">_TenantSignHere_</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n#Verhuurder#                                                              #Naam#<br/>\r\n<br/>\r\n<br/>\r\n<h3>Article 11.</h3>\r\nAfter signing by both parties this lease agreement is wholly legal.<br/>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\">\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td width=\"600\">\r\n            <h3> </h3>\r\n            <h3>General provisions</h3>\r\n            <p> </p>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3><b>associated with the lease on Rooms A, B, C and D, located in  #Woningmerk#.</b></h3>\r\n<h3>Chapter I. General</h3>\r\nThe tenant has rented according to the nature and destination of the leased property and respecting government prescribed requirements. <br/>\r\n<table>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td valign=\"top\" width=\"60\" align=\"center\"> 1. </td>\r\n            <td width=\"600\">\r\n            <p> tenant is, without written permission of the landlord, not authorized: <br/>\r\n            a) to fully or partially rent or sublet.<br/>\r\n            b) inact other activities than for which leased property is intended.</P>\r\n            </Td>\r\n        </Tr>\r\n    </Tbody>\r\n</Table>\r\n<table>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td valign=\"top\" width=\"60\" align=\"center\"> 2. </td>\r\n            <td width=\"600\"> The tenant may not use the associated storage areas for housing or for storage other than household objects, nor as a retail space.</td>\r\n        </Tr>\r\n    </Tbody>\r\n</Table>\r\n<table>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td valign=\"top\" width=\"60\" align=\"center\"> 3. </td>\r\n            <td width=\"600\">No rent will be due for the period that tenant could not use the room due to delayed departure of a previous tenant from the same room. Tenant declares to forego all rights he may have upon land lord in any such event.</Td>\r\n        </Tr>\r\n    </Tbody>\r\n</Table>\r\n\r\n<h3> Chapter II. State at the beginning and end of lease</H3>\r\n<table>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td valign=\"top\" width=\"60\" align=\"center\"> 1. </td>\r\n            <td width=\"600\">\r\n            <p>The starting condition and inventory of the apartment and room will be noted and be an annex to this contract.< / p>\r\n            </Td>\r\n        </Tr>\r\n    </Tbody>\r\n</Table>\r\n<table>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td valign=\"top\" width=\"60\" align=\"center\"> 2. </td>\r\n            <td width=\"600\">\r\n            <p>After termination of the contract, the renter will leave the apartment and room in the condition as accepted as the start of the contract.</p>\r\n            </Td>\r\n        </Tr>\r\n    </Tbody>\r\n</Table>\r\n<table>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td valign=\"top\" width=\"60\" align=\"center\"> 3. </td>\r\n            <td width=\"600\">\r\n            <p>At termination of the contract, land lord will perform an inspection of the apartment and room.</p>\r\n            </Td>\r\n        </Tr>\r\n    </Tbody>\r\n</Table>\r\n<table>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td valign=\"top\" width=\"60\" align=\"center\"> 4. </td>\r\n            <td width=\"600\">\r\n            <p>Damages and required repairs caused by the renter will be billed to him by the land lord. Land lord will provide detailed and motivated description of such repairs, including pictures of the state of the room before the tenant entered the contract.</p>\r\n            </Td>\r\n        </Tr>\r\n    </Tbody>\r\n</Table>\r\n<table>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td valign=\"top\" width=\"60\" align=\"center\"> 5. </td>\r\n            <td width=\"600\">\r\n            <p>Any material changes made by tenant will be reverted by him or her at termination of contract, unless there is agreement with land lord that such changes may remain.</P>\r\n            </Td>\r\n        </Tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td valign=\"top\" width=\"60\" align=\"center\"> 6. </td>\r\n            <td width=\"600\">\r\n            <p>The landlord or his representative shall have access to the apartment for inspection, which inspection - except in cases of emergency, will take place after consultation with the tenant. In the final rental month, after confirmed contract cancellation, the land lord has the right to viewings of the room to other prospective tenants, daily from 10:00 to 21:00. In addition, land lord has the regular right, at least one per six months and optionally in the presence of the tenant, to view the room for proper use.</p>\r\n            </Td>\r\n        </Tr>\r\n\r\n    </Tbody>\r\n</Table>\r\n\r\n<h3> Chapter VI. Central heating.</H3>\r\n<table>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td valign=\"top\" width=\"60\" align=\"center\"> 1. </td>\r\n            <td width=\"600\">\r\n            <p>The tenant will make sure the central heating system 